Level 1000 Galkovsky figure. "Albert Stopford". The British diplomat who took the regal insignia of the Romanovs in 1917 and secured it for the Windsors. Sneaked in through sewers to take "some of the most expensive items of jewelry ever to be created". Nothing is known about him

I think this is the only photograph of him that even exists. No details are known about his life. Had total diplomatic immunity during the Bolshevik revolution, took incalculable riches and escaped to London. Queen Elizabeth II wore the tiara he took. This is a real "James Bond".

Carl Schmitt says stuff like "the Lebensraum of an opera singer is different than the Lebensraum of a pilot" or "the element that manifested itself in the Luftwaffe was not Air, but Fire"... Otherwhere he hints that he believes in the Salamander fire elementals of Paracelsus...

Dr. Nikolai Vavilov had a theory called "Vavilovian mimicry" that cereal farming created new crops because when the farmer removed weeds from wheat he sometimes missed the weeds that most resembled wheat so eventually natural selection created secondary crops like rye and oats...

He just has dozens of these little bits and wordings that tend to stick with you, like Spengler's "brown laser" thing someone posted about a few months ago, Schmitt has the same feel as essays where the author composed them by connecting together twitter posts into one large text
They would produce the Antichrist...

Every idea of separation manifests in the phenomenon of selection in the real world... When you're not God and try to pick the sheep from the goats you always end up with a few sheep-like goats... And eventually you breed a new creature into existence from them... The sheep-goat.
